ascents.comment: Retrologging this now that it's been named, guess on date. Easiest of the 3 SICK lines Kenny showed us on his Kush Boulder. I spent about 15 min questing on the unclean V0 topout, and the only thing that kept me on was Mark telling me if I grabbed a rope at the top I didn't send. So that's probably where Kenny got the name... Awesome movement, beautiful tall line, full value from start to finish. Props to Kenny for discovering, cleaning, and giving me a shot at this thing! Come and get it.  P.S. I rarely FA, but when I do, it's soft. Video: https://vimeo.com/132502862

ascents.comment:
Without a doubt one of the proudest and hardest lines I have had the privilege of climbing on. The whole Sandbox came to give pads and support, and I surprised myself (and everyone else) by sending second go from the sit. Perfect conditions and a move that couldn't be more my style landed this in the 12 range for me. So damn psyched to take this down and continue taking on the never ending gauntlet set by Max, Mark, and all the Nor Cal crew. Happy fucking Halloween!

Edit: 200th double digit! Woohoo!

Actually felt pretty tame, psyched to get back to highballing!
